Do's and Don'ts for responsible social media use as a college student:-
1) Do's
- Use polite and respectful language while interacting online  
- Keep your profile professional and appropriate  
- Verify information before sharing or reposting  
- Use strong privacy settings to protect your account  
- Think before posting anything publicly  

2) Don’ts
- Do not share personal or sensitive information (phone, OTP, address)  
- Avoid posting offensive, harmful, or inappropriate content  
- Do not click on suspicious links or unknown messages  
- Avoid spreading fake news or unverified information  
- Do not engage in online arguments or negative discussions

